</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81CD70EB7B7FDF939EF7180" blockId="6.[207,1190,412,949]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
des Teppes de Verbois (bord du Rhône), Rus- Fig. 4. 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81CD70EB446FDFA3F1C711C" baseAuthorityName="Illiger" baseAuthorityYear="1807" box="[830,1071,581,602]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsessilis">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81CD70EB446FDFA3F1C711C" box="[830,1071,581,602]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Sphiximorpha subsessilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sur le tronc sin (GE), 
<date id="766AF5F6A81CD70EB63BFDD73A8071C5" box="[323,435,616,643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="2014-05-30">30.5.2014</date>
, sur un tronc d’un vieux d’un vieux 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81CD70EB41FFDE038DC7133" box="[871,1007,607,629]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81CD70EB41FFDE038DC7133" box="[871,1007,607,629]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Populus nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
au bord du Rhône dans la Réserve des Teppes de Verbois, Russin 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81CD70EB7B7FD353A4071E2" box="[207,371,650,676]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81CD70EB7B7FD353A4071E2" box="[207,371,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Populus nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vivant, leg. Jessica Castella. (GE), le 
<date id="766AF5F6A81CD70EB43EFD2C389171EF" box="[838,930,659,681]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" value="2014-05-30">30.5.2014</date>
. (Photo Jessica Castella) La présence de 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81CD70EB6A1FD12394D7180" baseAuthorityName="Illiger" baseAuthorityYear="1807" box="[473,638,684,711]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsessilis">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81CD70EB6A1FD12394D7180" box="[473,638,684,711]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">S. subsessilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n’avait
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81CD70EB7B7FD7138D770F2" blockId="6.[207,1190,412,949]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
jamais été confirmée jusqu’à présent (
<bibRefCitation id="6645AEC7A81CD70EB5F6FD71384F71AE" author="Maibach A. &amp; Goeldlin de Tiefenau P. &amp; Dirickx H. G." box="[654,892,718,745]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 51" refId="ref4560" refString="Maibach A., Goeldlin de Tiefenau P. &amp; Dirickx H. G. 1992. Liste faunistique des Syrphidae de Suisse (Diptera). Centre suisse de cartographie de la faune, Neuchatel. Miscellanea Faunistica Helvetiae 1: 1 - 51." type="journal article" year="1992">Maibach et al. 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Les adultes de cette es- pèce saproxylique passent de longs moments pratiquement immobiles sur les troncs d’arbres présentant des coulées de sève où leurs larves se développent. On les rencontre rarement ailleurs, bien qu’ils soient connus pour visiter les fleurs de 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81CD70EB355FC8A3F957009" box="[1069,1190,821,847]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Crataegus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81CD70EB355FC8A3F957009" box="[1069,1190,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Crataegus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et de 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81CD70EB660FCE93A5A7036" box="[280,361,854,880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Sorbus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81CD70EB660FCE93A5A7036" box="[280,361,854,880]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Sorbus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. En Europe centrale, 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81CD70EB502FCE838297036" baseAuthorityName="Illiger" baseAuthorityYear="1807" box="[634,794,854,881]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphiximorpha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subsessilis">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81CD70EB502FCE838297036" box="[634,794,854,881]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">S. subsessilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est une espèce particulièrement associée aux forêts alluviales à bois durs, bien que des groupes ou des lignes de 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81CD70EB7B7FC253A4570F2" box="[207,374,922,948]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81CD70EB7B7FC253A4570F2" box="[207,374,922,948]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Populus nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
très âgés puissent constituer des habitats alternatifs.
</paragraph>
